{{efn | name = never commissioned | Although the ''Kentucky'' was never [[ship commissioning|commissioned]] by the U.S. Navy, and therefore did not officially receive the USS ship prefix, she is conventionally referred to as USS ''Kentucky''. }}
{{efn | name = missiles | The addition of missiles to a battleship had already been done aboard the battleship {{USS|Mississippi|BB-41|2}} (BB-41/AG-128) to test the [[terrier missile]] after World War II. See {{harvnb|DANFS Mississippi (BB-41)}}. More recently, this was done to the four completed ''Iowa''-class battleships to allow them to carry and launch [[BGM-109 Tomahawk]] missiles and [[Boeing Harpoon|RGM-84 Harpoon missiles]]. ({{cite web | url = http://archive.gao.gov/f0102/115403.pdf | title = Update of the Issues Concerning the Proposed Reactivation of the Iowa class battleships and the Aircraft Carrier Oriskany | accessdate = 7 November 2007 | author = United States General Accounting Office | authorlink = Government Accountability Office | date = 20 April 1981 | format = PDF | publisher = United States General Accounting Office | pages = 3–18 }}) }}
